Malmö 2013: Petra Mede to host Eurovision 2013!
SVT, host broadcaster of Eurovision 2013, has announced that Petra Mede will be in charge of hosting the upcoming contest this May which will run over a total of three nights, on May 14th, 16th and 18th.
After Loreen’s Euphoric victory in Baku, SVT won the right to host the 2013 edition of the contest, and swiftly brought about changes to different areas of the contest. Within their role was selecting a host for the 2013 edition, and SVT announced just before midday that Petra Mede would be in charge of entertaining millions of viewers over the three night spectacle.
ESCDaily.com attended the event and would like to thank SVT for their assistance and hospitality.